<br>
Personally, I'm still having a blast with EQ. If they keep expanding and refining it's content, I will continue to do so.<br>
<br>
I believe the best thing that Verant can do to ensure the success of Everquest is to implement encounters where the users have more control over what's going on. Look at some encounters like the Ring of Fire, the Fungus Grove Caller Quest, the Plate House spawn force in Kael, etc. The first time I did the 10th Ring War (special thanks to Ibiza for telling me to get my ass over there and kill some giants <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), I was having an absolute blast. I thought the fact that the person initiating the quest had as much control as they did over what was going on was cool. Seeing 15 giants march in perfect formation and attack your party was cool. The whole encounter was just... cool. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
That's the kind of stuff that keeps this game fun for me. I haven't tried the Fungus Grove Caller quest or Ring of Fire yet, but I would love to. I'm sick of pulling mobs, I'd rather they charged me! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  There's a ton of room for content, and that's the reason I think the game will continue in it's success.<br>
<br>
What will the next expansion be? Will we find a passage to the underworld in the mines of Ak'anon? Will an alternate plane of existence be found, accessible through the Combine Ruins in DL? Who knows - it's impossible to say what Verant will do with EQ. If they keep the creative people that have made this game as fun as it is on their staff, the game will continue to attract new users and retain old ones.<br>
<br>
Also, I don't think that other games will really replace EQ. In my humble opinion, AO and DAoC helped this game more than they did hurt it. Verant was able to look at some of the things they were doing, copy it, and reproduce it in EQ. Since EQ already had two years of content in it, they were obviously more successful than the newer RPG's.<br>
<br>
I feel that if Verant continues to add game content, EQ will be around for a very, very long time. Who knows, we might even see an EQ2. <p><IMG SRC=http://www.tiannathomas.com/images/roliel3.gif>
