</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383836><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucarabellavalenteen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Carabella Valenteen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/7/02 3:25:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=353.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.dragonsong.org/immortalmercy/images/carabella22.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Better Question</span><hr size=1> I agree, Blearchie, I see server combines in the future as well.<br>
<br>
Oh, not for a long time!  But coming nonetheless.<br>
<br>
The cultural and social aspect of this game is enormous.  How many kids have stayed away from drugs because there was this 'game' to eat up their spare time?  How many marriages have been broken, all because of a 'game'?  How many friendships have made the transition from this 'game' to the real world?  How many RL friendships have ended because of ingame disputes?<br>
<br>
The impact of EQ to me, is mindboggling.  I look for it to continue for several years -- I am going to agree with the three year suggestion for the game to thrive, and then a total of five years before it begins to decline.  However, I think the game will be around indefinitely as people will be willing to pay forever, to maintain their characters.<br>
<br>
For me personally, I have a lot to see yet.  Cara has 4 levels to go (well, 3 1/2) till she reaches the level end of the game, and I have a lot of good friends to interact with.  As long as my friends are here, I shall be too.<br>
<br>
I give myself at least another year.<br>
<br>
Legends, to me, has marked the beginning of the end.  We shall see.<br>
<br>
